description:
tenacious. driven. exciting.

An avid client advocate, Jennifer Markus does not take her role and responsibilities as a broker lightly. With an impeccable track record in sales, an ingrained sense of duty to her clients, and a real estate career spanning over two decades, Jennifer’s approach always ensures that her buyers and sellers come first.

Originally from Canada, Jennifer kicked off her sales career in the high-end jewelry industry in Boca Raton, Florida. Naturally, this skill set transferred seamlessly into her career as a broker, as Jennifer has always had a talent for making her clients feel comfortable and happy with major purchases. From then on, Jennifer spent years cultivating the knowledge and experience — both as a broker and a broker/owner — that is essential for crafting her harmonious approach.

Jennifer uses a combination of high-level communication, comprehensive preparation, and skillful guidance to ensure her buyers and sellers know what to expect at every stage of the transaction. This prowess has positioned Jennifer as a dominating force in Denver’s south suburban corridor in the high-end luxury price point. Additionally, Jennifer has always worked alongside her husband, Todd — an integral part of the Markus team who assists in all aspects of the business.

Professional Proficiencies
// Luxury Sales in South Denver
// High-Level Communication + Support
// Expert Preparation + Guidance

Jennifer spends much of her free time finding the next great coffee shop, discovering a new wine bar, or taking a stroll with her beloved border collie, Calvin. When she’s not out and about traveling or e-biking through Denver, Jennifer finds serenity in her flower garden.

Personal Passions
// Causes that Support Animal Welfare
// Tending to Her Flower Garden
// Finding the Next Best Spot in Denver
